To build, install the prerequisites. Then

/bin/sh ./configure
gmake

Install with

gmake install


PREREQUISITES
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* the Gnu make utility
  (no, I definitely don't like it; but what can you do, it's too widespread)

  tested with Version 3.81, but should work with others as well
  http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/make/make-3.81.tar.bz2
  SHA256 (make-3.81.tar.bz2) = f3e69023771e23908f5d5592954d8271d3d6af09693cecfd29cee6fde8550dc


* ocaml

  tested with 3.11.2, but should also with other versions

  http://caml.inria.fr/distrib/ocaml-3.11/ocaml-3.11.2.tar.bz2
  SHA256 (ocaml-3.11.2.tar.bz2) = 86f3387a0d7e7c8be2a3c53af083a5a726e333686208d5ea0dd6bb5ac3f58143

* python

  Tested with Version 2.6.6, but should work with other python 2.x was well

  http://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.6.6/Python-2.6.6.tgz
  SHA256 (Python-2.6.6.tgz) = 372f66db46d773214e4619df1794a26449158f626138d4d2141a64c2f017fae1

Additional configure Options
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

--with-doc

  Provide some form of documentation. The location where the documentation is to be installed to
  can be set with the --doc-dir option. The default location exapnds to ../doc/pycaml
